Fill and boil your #kettle{} (for your sauce later on).

Bring a #large saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the
potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (peel first if you prefer).

When boiling, add the potatoes to the water and cook until you can easily
slip a knife through, about ~{12-15%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a
#colander{} and return to the #pot{}, off the heat. Cover with a #lid{} to
keep warm.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high
heat.

Once hot, add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

Cook until golden on the outside, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken cooks, halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(halved,
peeled and thinly sliced).

Roughly chop the @chives{1%bunch}(roughly chopped) (use scissors if easier).

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic
press).

Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}(thinly sliced).

Once the chicken is browned, add the onion and sliced mushrooms to the pan.

Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Cook until the mushrooms
have browned and the onion has softened, ~{6-7%minutes}, stirring occasionally.

Add your garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

Once the veggies are soft, add the @plain flour{1%tbsp} and stir to coat
evenly.

Pour in @water{150%ml} from the kettle, stirring to combine. Stir in the
@red wine jus paste{22%g}, then bring back to the boil.

Simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}, then remove from the heat and stir in half the
chives.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Taste and add salt and pepper if needed. Add a splash of water if it's a bit
thick.

Add a knob of @butter{}, a splash of @?milk{} and the
@grated hard italian style cheese{40%g} to your cooked potatoes, then mash
with a #potato masher{} until smooth.

Season to taste with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}.

Serve the cheesy mash in #bowls{} with the chicken stew on top and a
sprinkling of the remaining chives. Enjoy!

> STEP 2 MOD: If you've chosen to get chicken breast instead of chicken thigh,
> cook the recipe in the same way the instructions tell you to cook the chicken thigh.